C.pj=new N.ee("Head of Mobile","Ciklum","april 2018","present","As a Head of Mobile Stack I:",C.rN)
C.tq=H.b(s(["I managed developers from iOS, Android, and cross-platform stacks. I owned the competence development process (assessment, education, certification, knowledge sharing, community development);","I responded for the alignment between personal development plans of each talent in the Mobile team with Ciklum's strategy;","Implemented a built-in quality approach across all mobile teams (including implementation of engineering practices, shared services, and technical audit process);"]),t.i)
C.pf=new N.ee("Mobile Technical Lead","Ciklum","january 2017","april 2018","While still acting as a cross-platform mobile developer, I had more administrative activities.",C.tq)
C.tl=H.b(s(["I developed cross-platform mobile applications in C#. Worked with F#, Objective-C, Swift, and Java. My target OS were iOS, Android, WP7, WP8, and UWP (Windows 10). Frameworks I used: Xamarin, Xamarin.Forms, FreshMvvm, Reactive Extensions, ReactiveProperty, RxUI, MvvmCross. I worked via TDD using NUnit, MSTest, and Moq. For a few projects used BDD with Calabash and Ruby. I acted as the chief reviewer during code reviews.","My primary responsibilities were team coaching and technical quality assurance. I improved and automated the internal processes: CI, metrics, workflows, and other best practices. I have conducted internal and external interviews.","I made estimations, participated in workshops, project, and proposal reviews. Supervised and participated in technology investigations and researches. Consulted client-side developers, responded for high-level architecture for projects."]),t.i)
C.ph=new N.ee("Xamarin Lead Dev","Ciklum","november 2012","december 2016","On this position, I was in charge not only for the software development but for the team.",C.tl)
